def: Becoming; suitable. [Archaic] -- Be*seem"ing*ly, adv.-- Be*seem"ing*ness, n.
Having a blunt or button-shaped extremity; -- said of cuttinginstruments.
One who keeps a tavern. Chaucer. Camden.
, Divided into bars; -- said of the field.
A kind of Italian pressed milk cheese; -- so called from avillage near Milan.
The doctrines, notions, or practice of Puritans.
Having the point or top cut off. [Obs.] Bailey.
